<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="555" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 738.3915/112a.]</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Dominican Minister</gloss>.</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d555fn1">The same, mutatis mutandis, to the Haitian
                                Minister.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-26">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: In view of the fact that
                            the Minister of Haiti is now in receipt of new full powers to negotiate
                            concerning the Dominican-Haitian boundary dispute, I should be glad to
                            have the plenipotentiaries meet at the Department of State at 10 o’clock
                            Saturday morning, April 27th, for the purpose of renewing active
                            negotiations, and I shall be happy to be present at the meeting.</p>
                        <p>I have informed the Minister of Haiti in like sense.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.].</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>